  "description": "Atoms emitted by the RE covert-scan skills (js-covert-scan, py-covert-scan), not by the signature packs. These name obfuscation / environment-keyed evasion / steganography tactics -- families the judgment-free MCD ontology deliberately omits (it uses XFRM for transformation, ENVI for environment interaction; obfuscation / evasion would be lens judgments). They live here, in a dedicated registry, so a scanner core can validate a skill-emitted atom by EXACT ATOM rather than a family whitelist. Each entry carries the family, a default confidence baseline, a mechanical one-line description, and which skill(s) emit it. As with all such signals, any single atom can be legitimate; the strong signal is co-occurrence.",
